Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-cz] <yorklab> In the Agama Lite wallet if you have a different address it was because a different passphrase was used. When creating a new wallet copy the address then please be sure you can log back in using the same passphrase and check that it's the same address before transferring any funds into that wallet.

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-cz] <yorklab> This would apply to any wallet used.

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-cz] <PTYX> If you didn't export your privatekey, or your seed file is encrypted and you can't decrypt it, then there is little we can do. I use Pungo and it works fine. It's based on the Agama seed generation.
